# Commit message format

When creating a git commit, **always** prefix the commit message with `CU-[clickup task id]` followed by a space, then the rest of the message.

If the user has mentioned a ClickUp task ID in the conversation (e.g. `869c9qwdy`), use that ID. If no task ID has been mentioned, ask the user for the ClickUp task ID before committing.

Example:

```
CU-869c9qwdy Fix supplement calculation to compare per line item
```
